OL,5,Creport
OL,7,F"If the court backlog is to be tackled
OL,8,Fand the public are to regain
OL,9,Fconfidence in the system there needs
OL,10,Fto be sufficient workforce to meet the
OL,11,Fdemands. The next government needs to
OL,12,Fstep up to the plate. It would cost
OL,13,Fthe public purse peanuts in the scale
OL,14,Fof overall government spending to
OL,15,Fensure every case has a barrister on
OL,16,Feach side. This investment would save
OL,17,Fconsiderably more than is spent
OL,18,Fbecause there would be far fewer
OL,19,Fineffective trials," he said.
